				<p>The picture of the two of you is adorable. My husband and I stayed at the Hilton (I think) just next to the Eiffel Tower for three days last fall. It was supposed to be 7 days &#8211; and for him it was (he had to be there for a conference). As for me, well, I&#8217;ll just say &#8211; make absolutely sure your passport is current before stepping up to the Air France ticket counter.</p>
<p>But, my tragically foreshortened three days were wonderful. Our best day was spent just wandering around the Ile St. Louis. I&#8217;ve been dying to ask you, Deb, if you ate at the Mon Martin boulangerie on the main street there &#8211; moving away from Notre Dame it is about the third one. They had the best Napoleons / Mille Fuielle (Aggghh &#8211; this is spelled wrong) I&#8217;ve ever had. Something about the almost, but not quite, burnt pastry combined wonderfully with the cream filling; much better than anemic underbaked pastry that you usually encounter with them. </p>
<p>Can we look forward to a Napoleon recipe? I&#8217;ve been waiting for a really good one in order to attempt them.</p>
